Activists say they’re determined to hold accountable those behind a R4.5-billion development. eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Indigenous and environmental activists want the developers behind a multi-billion-rand development on the banks of Liesbeek River in Cape Town arrested. They claim the developers are in contempt of a high court order prohibiting construction. WATCH: Court halts Amazon HQ development But the Liesbeek Leisure Property Trust is going ahead with construction, citing a case at the Supreme Court of Appeal. * eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports.